Twentieth Century Fox has released a new trailer for the next installment of the Planet of the Apes franchise, which pits the leaders of the apes and humans against each other in an epic face-off.In the two-minute trailer for &#8220;War for the Planet of the Apes,&#8221; humans and apes draw their weapons in a battle that will determine the fate of both their species. &#8220;I did not start this war,&#8221; says Caesar in the opening scene.&#8220;I offered you peace. I showed you mercy. But now you&#8217;re here to finish us off. For good.&#8221; For his part, the Colonel justifies war by saying: &#8220;This is our last stand. And if we lose, it will be a planet of apes.&#8221;The film is directed by Matt Reeves and stars Andy Serkis, Woody Harrelson, Steve Zahn, Karin Konoval, Amiah Miller and Terry Notary.&#8220;War for the Planet of the Apes&#8221; opens July 14, 2017.-Relaxnews